node.text:
Go behind the design with Nike Materials Designer Francesca Capone-Jones (@franny_capone) and environmental journalist Sophia Li (@sophfei) as they break down the details discussing how two iconic Nike styles were reimagined with sustainability in mind.

Skip Around:
Catch up on Nike's Move to Zero initiative with Sophia Li and meet Nike Materials Designer, Francesca Capone-Jones (3:55), as she breaks down the innovation behind the all new Air Force 1 Crater and Waffle Racer Crater (10:50). Plus, get a crash course from a pro on the principles of sustainable design (30:45) before hearing Francesca answer questions from the audience (38:45). 

Shop AF1 Crater and Waffle Crater: 
http://smarturl.it/craterbts

Growing up in South Africa, @karabo_poppy was obsessed with art, but couldn’t find herself or her experiences reflected in it.
⠀
Karabo uses unconventional canvases like basketball courts and city streets—things people interact with in their everyday life. That’s why she is so drawn to the Air Force 1 for her artwork.
⠀
This season, Karabo’s artwork graces the Air Force 1 through Nike By You. #af1 #allfor1 #nikebyyou

node.text: Up for something different? Hooping enthusiast Cynthia gives a step-by-step intro to her long-time passion. Give it a go and tell us how it goes 👇🏿 #nikedunkhigh

Spotlight on Paris street gamers 🪀 🤸🏽‍♀️ and the eclectic passions that have brought them together.

Introducing the crew making forgotten disciplines of the past popular once again: Quentin, a yo-yoer known for his artistic, impressive, risky figures. Williams, know for his fast, technical, combo yo-yo style. Chippi, an electronics student turned globe-trotting juggler. Tybald, an aspiring pro circus performer. Coco, a contortionist “breaking the box stereotype” and Cynthia, long-time hooping enthusiast.

Tag your crew bringing back a lost passion.🔥

Crew wears #nikedunkhigh in White and Midnight Navy.

“When I step on the court, I definitely want to stand out.” -@serenawilliams✨

An innovator since day one, Serena changed the tennis world, then saw a need to change the world of design, too.

So, allow us to introduce: the Serena Williams Design Crew.⚡️

By championing diverse talent from all walks of life, Serena and her ten up-and-coming design teammates will be catalysts for change.🤝 Head to our 🔗 in bio to learn more about the program.
